The article highlights that core inflation has reached its lowest level in two years, while overall inflation has dropped by 60% from its peak. This has occurred despite unemployment remaining below 4% for 20 consecutive months and the highest workforce participation rate in 20 years. The article attributes these positive economic indicators to the policies of the Biden administration, which aims to build an economy that benefits the middle class and lower-income individuals. However, it also mentions that Republicans in Congress are threatening to weaken the economy by prioritizing tax cuts for the wealthy and large corporations, as well as proposing deep cuts to programs that support hardworking Americans and seniors.